 Sal: I taught high to earn some money. 

00:06:18.270 --> 00:06:22.318
 I worked as an MCAT instructor for a year at the University of Princeton 

00:06:22.318 --> 00:06:27.067
 and I also taught second grade students at Devotion School in Brookline. 

00:06:27.067 --> 00:06:33.385
 I enjoyed it, but the economy and the investment funds were a little bit more fun. 

00:06:33.385 --> 00:06:42.336
 Robert: Could you create a video comparing the investment fund analyst's and the teacher's salary. 

00:06:42.336 --> 00:06:49.201
 Real-time communication with students does not work in online learning. 

00:06:49.201 --> 00:06:56.118
 Do you think this may be another plus in teaching? Does it play a role? 

00:06:56.118 --> 00:06:59.802
 Sal: I think that's the advantage I have over traditional teachers 

00:06:59.802 --> 00:07:07.285
 judging by my experience with traditional teaching. One of the hardest things to do is sit against a class of 20-30 pupils 

00:07:07.285 --> 00:07:12.351
 of which five seem to perceive you. The rest are just staring at you 

00:07:12.351 --> 00:07:16.668
 and you do not know if they are bored or they do not follow the interpretation. It makes you uneasy and you don't know what to do. 

00:07:16.668 --> 00:07:21.901
 I will explain something to my computer in ten minutes, as if to explain it to you or your cousin, 

00:07:21.901 --> 00:07:26.951
 and then upload it to YouTube. It takes about half an hour. 

00:07:26.951 --> 00:07:34.168
 In the first hour of uploading a video, a hundred people watch the video, and I wait to see if five stars 

00:07:34.168 --> 00:07:40.451
 and write to him "that's great" or "I can handle the tomorrow's test" or anything else. 

00:07:40.451 --> 00:07:44.535
 I'm waiting for feedback from viewers. That will give me the courage to work on. 

00:07:44.535 --> 00:07:52.735
 Robert: Salman Khan, lecturer in mathematics, science, economics and many other things at khanacademy.org. 

